Jacques Chirac &apos;s political legacy endures
Former French President Jacques Chirac died at the age of 86 .
At a time when the world is in the grip of a century of unprecedented change , the French statesman still deserves credit for the many political legacies he left in office .
Mr Chirac has been France &apos;s president for 12 years in a charismatic role .
He inherited Gaullist independence of the diplomatic spirit , but also firmly support European integration , is a representative of the pursuit of the &quot; European dream &quot; .
At the same time , he was a strong advocate of world multipolarity and multilateralism , and a strategically minded politician .
He was described in the French press as &quot; France &apos;s outstanding representative on the world stage &quot; .
One of Chirac &apos;s most popular political decisions was his opposition to the American-led war in Iraq .
Under his leadership , France joined Germany in the face of American pressure and went to the forefront of the anti-war movement .
A year after the war broke out , he predicted that the war in Iraq would lead to an intensification of terror and make the world more dangerous .
As it turned out , Chirac ’ s warning was correct .
At a time when European integration is at a loss and American unilateralism is on the rise , Chirac ’ s strategic thinking and decisions on international politics and global affairs are of great enlightenment .
Chirac is also a French statesman who makes the Chinese feel familiar and affectionate .
He was one of the initiators and creators of the &quot; Golden Decade &quot; between China and France . After his first election as President of France in 1995 , he promoted the rapid development of China-France relations with the strategic vision of statesmen .
In 2004 , China and France established a comprehensive strategic partnership .
Under Chirac &apos;s administration , bilateral trade between China and France grew rapidly , and the two countries have made breakthroughs in many areas , including aviation , nuclear energy and rail transport .
Chirac initiated the Year of Sino-French Culture , creating a completely new cultural exchange pattern in the history of China and France .
Chirac &apos;s lifelong devotion to Chinese culture was particularly impressive .
Chirac can memorize some poems by Li Bai and Du Fu , and even accurately judge the historical age of Chinese bronzes , according to Chinese diplomats who know him .
&quot; Not looking at the pyramids , not really going to Egypt , not looking at the Qin Terracotta Army , not really going to China &quot; - the gold phrase comes from Chirac .
&quot; The West is concerned about China &apos;s political and social development , ecological issues arising from China &apos;s economic growth and China &apos;s political position in the world , &quot; Chirac said in an exclusive interview with Xinhua .
But I myself have confidence in China .
I believe that China is a country with a long history of civilization , and that its experience is sufficient to help it establish the concepts and values for harmonious development and assume its responsibilities on the world stage for a long time to come .
I also believe that China &apos;s renaissance will bring new creative energy to world culture and enrich world culture .
The Sri Lankans are gone , but Chirac &apos;s legacy and enlightenment to the world will endure .
