On September 26 , 2006 , Chinese State Councilor and Foreign Minister Wang Yi chaired the meeting of Foreign Ministers of China and African member states of the UN Security Council at the UN headquarters in New York .
The Ministers for Foreign Affairs of the current member states of the Security Council in Africa , Côte d &apos;Ivoire ( Tano ) , Equatorial Guinea ( Oyono ) , South Africa ( Pandor ) , Niger ( Kalla ) and Tunisia ( Jishnawi ) attended the meeting .
Wang Yi made four proposals on strengthening China-Africa cooperation in the Security Council .
First , by uniting our forces .
The biggest challenge in the current international situation is unilateralism . As a direct consequence , the basic norms governing international relations have been challenged , and the role of the United Nations has been undermined , to the detriment of the interests of developing countries , small and medium-sized countries , including African countries .
The response to this challenge requires the strength of unity , hand in hand and side by side with the Central African Republic .
In the Security Council , where the three African countries speak with one voice , the weight of the focus is not just on three votes , but on the continent as a whole .
By standing together , China and Africa will not be just four votes , but will lead other countries to follow suit , influencing and shaping the Council &apos;s agenda .
Since 2018 , China and African members of the Security Council have established the &quot; 3 + 1 &quot; coordination mechanism , which should be fully utilized .
Secondly , to settle disputes by negotiation .
China has always advocated political settlement of hotspot issues.Africa has a good tradition of consultation and the experience of successful mediation by African regional and sub-regional organizations .
Many of the complex dilemmas on the Council &apos;s agenda , in particular the hot spots in Africa , are mostly rooted in colonialism or are directly related to external factors .
We should make joint use of Chapter VI of the UN Charter to bring into play the role of the UN in mediation and mediation .
Third , rely on independence to seek self-improvement .
African countries and peoples know their problems best , and Africa has the capacity and wisdom to solve its own .
In dealing with hot issues in Africa , the Council should focus on listening to and respecting the will of Africa , should play the role of regional and subregional organizations , and should encourage and support endogenous solutions from Africa .
China is ready to strengthen coordination with Africa and firmly promote the capacity building of African independent peace operations .
Fourthly , development is fundamental to the rule of law .
China and African countries are both developing countries.We must put economic and social development first and support each other in the road of development that we have chosen .
China is ready to work closely with the African Union Agenda 2063 , the United Nations 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development and the development strategies of African countries to help them enhance their capacity for development and eliminate the root causes of conflicts .
We should jointly urge the United Nations to increase its investment in Africa &apos;s development .
China has made and will continue to make every effort to provide assistance , provide human and material assistance within its capacity , coordinate actions with African countries , mobilize the United Nations and WHO to increase their aid efforts , and give full play to the role of the United Nations Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of the Congo ( MONUSCO ) .
Neonatology , such as relay to save small lives .
Thrilling !
The expectant mother had an early attack , and on the way to the hospital , a 32-week-old baby was born in her father &apos;s car .
Thanks to the timely management of obstetrics and neonatal paediatricians , this little life was saved .
Coincidentally , on the 19th , 20th , and 21st , the obstetrics and neonatology departments of Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Center received three babies on the road three days in a row , the other two were both born in 120 emergency vehicles , both at 29 weeks .
At 7 : 00 a.m. on Sept . 19 , feeling a pain in her stomach and thinking she was 32 weeks pregnant and that her first baby had been born prematurely , Ms. Cheng packed up her maternity supplies and went straight to the hospital after taking a bath .
At 9 : 30 , Mrs. Cheng packed up and let her husband drive from her home in Xudong to the hospital .
Not long before the car leaves the house , baby can not wait to be born in the father &apos;s car .
After 20 minutes , Ms. Cheng and her baby finally arrived at the obstetrics and gynecology building of the Hubei Provincial Maternal and Child Health Center .
The hospital security guard saw the frantic couple and baby , immediately notified the maternity ward , deputy chief doctor Zhang Huan and other four doctors and midwife Liu Yan , carrying the baby bag and umbilical cord dish rushed downstairs .
&quot; At that time , the woman was half lying on the side of the car , with the water of amniotic fluid and blood , and a baby boy next to her , with the umbilical cord still attached .
Zhang Huan asked to learn that the baby is a 32-week premature baby , on the way to the parents did not have time to cover the package for the child , early autumn morning has cold , he froze pale skin , no crying , four limbs collapse .
Liu Yanyan hurried to the vice driving to handle the baby &apos;s umbilical cord , Zhang Huan got into the cab , quickly opened the delivery bag , wrapped several layers of warm with the inside therapeutic towel and bag cloth , and cleaned the newborn &apos;s airway ( pictured ) , then took the baby to the neonatology unit on the 12th floor .
When the neonatology medical care learned the news , immediately rushed to the nurses to save the premature baby on the spot .
At that time , the baby blue face , a condition of suffocation oxygen , the doctor immediately made him a trachea intubation , less than a minute , the baby resumed a heartbeat , the color of the skin gradually returned to rosy , successful resuscitation .
After admission , the 32-week-old baby was put on a ventilator and was resuscitated the next day .
After a week of treatment , the baby &apos;s vital signs are stable , breathing is smooth , and a small amount of breast feeding has begun .
On 19 , 20 , and 21 December , the obstetrics and neonatology department received three children born on the road , two of whom were born in 120 emergency vehicles , both at 29 weeks of age .
Sun Guoqiang , director of obstetrics at the provincial maternal and child health hospital , said that in recent years , mothers and children had received many babies born on the subway or in private cars .
Sun reminded that pregnant mothers should come to the hospital immediately if they have abdominal pain , broken water , see red , etc .
If in the home or on the way to the basin , the mother should lie down as far as possible , can be padded in the buttock blanket , etc. to prevent the baby from hitting the ground after birth , immediately after childbirth to keep warm , as soon as possible to be sent to the nearest doctor .
