China News Agency Baoshan , September 27 ( Zhang Weiming Xu for the State of Zhou Jingbo ) after more than 1,200 days of day and night construction , the Dawei ( Li ) Rui ( Li ) Railway Gaoligongshan Tunnel No. 1 shaft completed construction on the 27th , at the depth of 762.59 meters below the surface , breaking the China Railway Tunnel shaft shaft , which is the deepest record , and this record is created by a large amount of water rush .
The 34.5 km long Daligongshan Tunnel is located in Yunnan , and is the longest single-tunnel tunnel in Asia , crossing the Gaoligongshan Mountains from the western bank of the Nujiang River .
The tunnel traverses 19 fault zones , with a maximum depth of 1,155 metres ( 3,430 ft ) , and is known as the &quot; Geology Museum &quot; of the tunnel construction because it covers almost all of the geological hazards and major risks that would be encountered in the construction of the tunnel .
The shaft is the most important auxiliary tunnel of the Gaoligongshan Tunnel , which is charged with the important task of increasing the operating surface to realize the &quot; short tunnel &quot; and the late railway operation ventilation .
The number 1 shaft was successfully dug to the bottom of the well , marking the formal entry of the Gaoligongshan Tunnel into the horizontal tunnel construction .
&quot; The shaft is all in the granite formation , because granite formation crevasses are more , can not stop the water , from the top to the bottom flow , basically as deep as the water pressure well . &quot;
Dai Jingzhao , Chief Engineer of the Dali Railway Project Department of China Railway Tunnel Bureau , told reporters that the shaft construction , many times occurred , such as muddy rush water , collapse , the construction side invited experts to the scene of the pulse , more than 20 to discuss the treatment plan .
&quot; At its maximum , the pressure of water in the shaft is equal to more than 300 cubic metres per hour , at a depth of more than 700 metres at the bottom of the well . &quot;
&quot; If we don &apos;t drain the water in time , we will drown 10 meters in one hour , &quot; he said . &quot; We spend almost 85 percent of our time on water treatment and 15 percent of our time on digging . &quot;
In order to overcome such geologic problems as longitudinal joint development , water inrush , water-rich granite , etc . , the tunnel construction adopts the combination of exploration , injection and excavation to reduce the risk of construction .
After many improvements , the construction of shaft No. 1 has formed a mechanized pipeline , such as excavation system , ballast system , hoist system , winch lifting system , etc . , and has realized the mechanization of the whole process , such as drilling , blasting , ballast , template installation , concrete pouring , etc . , thus accelerating the construction progress .
Eventually , after more than 1200 days of day and night construction , the shaft was successfully completed at a depth of 762.59 m .
