From next year , Chinese students will be able to apply for German undergraduate courses based on their results in the college entrance examination
Starting in 2020 , Chinese high school graduates can apply directly to German universities for undergraduate degrees based on their scores in the college entrance examination , without first enrolling in a domestic university , Germany &apos;s Anabin database , which evaluates foreign qualifications , announced on its website .
Before that , Chinese high school graduates who wanted to apply to a German university needed to study for one semester ( 211,985 university ) or three semesters ( regular undergraduate ) at home , and pass either the APS or the TestAS examination .
The new rules could save at least half a year for Chinese students who want to study in Germany .
The new rules are expected to come into force in the second half of 2019 .
Applicants are required to : complete 12 years of compulsory formal education and obtain a senior secondary school diploma ; take the entrance examination , college entrance examination , and attain a score of 70 % or above of the total score ( 525 or above if the total score is 750 ) , and include two language grades and one grade in mathematics or natural sciences .
In addition , the specific professional requirements for college entrance examination results are not the same .
For example , to apply for a major in medicine , oral medicine , veterinary medicine , pharmacy , etc . , a score of 80 % of the full mark must be obtained , and the subject must include at least two subjects in mathematics , physics , chemistry , biology , or integration in science ; to apply for a major in law , a score of 80 % of the full mark must be obtained , and the subject must include a foreign language , history , at least two subjects in geography , or participation in literature .
According to incomplete statistics , there have been a number of countries including Germany , the United Kingdom , Canada , Australia and other countries recognized Chinese college entrance examination results .
In the UK , universities such as Cambridge University , Birmingham University , and Leicester University all accept applications from Chinese students based on their GCE results .
