It is understood that the Regulations were revised on the basis of the Measures for the Implementation of the Law of the People &apos;s Republic of China on the Protection of the Rights and Interests of Women in Ningxia in 2007 , which is divided into 9 chapters and 65 articles , including general provisions , political rights , rights and interests in culture and education , rights and interests in labor and social security , rights and interests in property , personal rights , rights in marriage and family , legal responsibilities and supplementary regulations .
In the Regulations , Ningxia encouraged the exploration of joint parental leave , which was the first in China .
