Consultation on the new regulations : social capital to acquire rural land management rights to be qualified
Social Capital Acquire Rural Land Management Rights to Be Qualified
&quot; Measures on the Management of the Transfer of Rural Land Management Rights &quot; to be published for consultation and to supervise the transfer of social capital , such as industrial and commercial enterprises , to acquire the right to manage land
Yesterday , the website of the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs published a notice on the &quot; Measures on the Management of the Transfer of Rural Land Management Rights ( Draft for Exposure to Exposure ) &quot; ( hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Draft Opinion &quot; ) to solicit public comments , adding supervision and risk prevention for the acquisition of land management rights by businesses and other social capital transfers .
The draft of the Opinions is now open for public consultation .
According to the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development , in order to implement the newly revised Law on Rural Land Contracting , further consolidate and improve the basic rural management system , deepen the reform of the rural land system and implement the &quot; division of three powers &quot; system , the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs revised the &quot; Measures on the Transfer and Management of Rural Land Contracting Rights &quot; , resulting in the &quot; Opinions &quot; .
Beijing Youth Daily reporters learned that the first published &quot; Opinions &quot; have a number of important changes .
The newly revised Law on Rural Land Contracting clarifies the scope of land transfer , implements the concept of &quot; division of three rights &quot; , establishes separate sections on &quot; land contracting and management rights &quot; and makes a clear distinction between the transfer of land contracting and management rights and the transfer of land management rights ( through leasing , subcontracting , share ownership or other means ) .
In order to implement the concept of &quot; division of the three powers &quot; and effectively respond to the main points of the Law on the revision of the Law on Rural Land Contracting , and taking into account the fact that the transfer of land management rights and the exchange of land management rights are quite different in terms of the parties involved , procedures and supervision , the revised Draft defined the scope of the transfer of land management rights , focusing on the transfer of land management rights in the form of leasing , stock ownership , etc . , and changed the name of the Regulation from &quot; Measures for the Administration of the Transfer of Rural Land Contract Management Rights &quot; to &quot; Measures for the Transfer of Rural Land Management Rights &quot; .
The transfer and exchange of land contract management right will be separately regulated .
The draft notes that , in the context of the &quot; division of three powers &quot; , farmers only own shares in the land for a limited period of time .
Theoretically , there is no longer any legal need to return the contracted land to the original contractor , but there is also a conflict with the Bankruptcy Law .
Aiming at the problem of preventing the risk of peasants losing their land , the practice has produced the methods of preferred shares , lease shares first , buy back , and so on .
Considering that the preferred shares have been discussed in the company law , it is suggested that it should be used as an advocacy provision to prevent the risk of losing land .
